    p.btext When I was twenty-seven years old, I was a mining-broker's clerk in San Francisco, and an expert in all the details of stock traffic. I was alone in the world, and had nothing to depend upon but my wits and a clean reputation; but these were setting my feet in the road to eventual fortune, and I was content with the prospect.

    br

    p
      span.btext My time was my own
      |
      |(мое время было моим собственным = у меня было свободное время)
      |
