    p.btext My time was my own after the afternoon board, Saturdays, and I was accustomed to put it in on a little sail-boat on the bay. One day I ventured too far, and was carried out to sea. Just at nightfall, when hope was about gone, I was picked up by a small brig which was bound for London. It was a long and stormy voyage, and they made me work my passage without pay, as a common sailor.

    br

    p
      span.btext When I stepped ashore in London
      |
      |(когда я ступил на берег в Лондоне;
      |
      span.f-coni ashore [q'SO:]
      |)
      |
